task.summary: Default task
Now the installer bundles DualSPHysics and preconfigures DesignSPHysics to use it.
Preparing BETA 0.2 release
Changed XML dump to show app name, not case name in app property, as it should.
Started implementing wave generators on the interface. Quite buggy for now
Wave generators finished. Probably buggy, yet to be tested.
Now 'Import XML' warns the user of the experimental nature of the functionality.
Reworked Object Order table.
Changed some units text and removed case limits overgrowing on save. This way you can make a 2D case setting the width of the case limits object to less or equal than DP
Added some warning texts to motion. Prevented case limits rotation. Changed batch file generation to a template driven one. Preparing for testing and release.
Preparing for release

Fixed floatings in STL scaling. Now it works Fixed some cases in which the simulation object order table would display an additional row, breaking its functionality Fixed DualSPHysics4 recognition in GNU/Linux. LD_LIBRARY_PATH was not set and cudart lib was missing.
Executable paths no longer get loaded from a file if you already have correct ones Export to VTK is now disabled if you cancel the running simulation
Complex meshes can now be used as fluids (only with face mode)
Added case summary functionality. Not finished yet.
Fixed an error where an object with movement enabled but no movements selected caused saving to fail.
Fixed a critical error in movements that caused multiple movements to fail
First version of case summary. Has a bit of everything but not in detail
Fixed an error with default values in execution parameters that made them appear commented. Reworked execution parameters setup window to have selectors in options with discrete values.
Implemented 2D/3D toggle for case limits.
Implemented regular wave generator disk saving features.
Implemented saving features to all wave generators. Needs fine tuning
Implemented movement generatos from file. Made some changes that will make previous cases not work with the new version.
Implemented browse button for file based movements. Started implemented new post-processing tools.
Implemented partvtk post-processing with options
Implemented automatic file opening with paraview at end of PartVTK usage. It searches paraview in the common installation folder and tries to open it with the output data.
Started draft of ComputeForces, FloatingInfo and MeasureTool export windows.
Added custom file names for PartVTK tool exporting. Changed roadmap a bit

Changed movement from file behaviour. Now it automatically tries to copy the movement definition file and point the path to the newly created one.
Implemented additional command-line parameters for PartVTK in the export dialog.

First iteration of FloatingInfo export.
Added shapeout by default in XML export.
Included new post-processing tools in plugin setup window and data structure. May not be compatible with previous versions.
Added ComputeForces post processing tool
Implemented MeasureTool post processing tool

Cosmetic changes
Changes _Out folder suffix with _out (capitalization). Changes Save & Run GenCase dialog a bit.
Adds FlowTool to Case Summary

Various fixes and additions
Fixes typos in case summary. Adds new type of info dialog for post-processing. Disables batch script generation. Changes texts on some components.

Filters move and rotate commands on the XML
They no longer appear if the values don't make any difference.
Now STL files are referenced with relative paths
Changes AWAS config labels to show units
Adds Slice or Surface selector to IsoSurface post-processing tool
Adds mk/id/position selector to ComputeForces export
Changes open with paraview button from save menu

Makes details dialog on GenCase saving a popup.
Hacked through the garbage collector to do it, so the menu appears when the dialog is not modal, avoiding using exec_()
Fixes FlowTool point order and changes the reference image

Removes space restrictions on save path
DualSPHysics now supports paths with spaces on it, so there's no need to keep DesignSPHysics forcing the users to save in a folder which path contains no spaces.
Fixes #18

Implements FlowTool executable check
Now when the FlowTool executable is missing or incorrect the application will try to load one from the config file and warn the user.

Change save menu and procedure to separate GenCase execution from saving
Added paraview path to the setup. Re-enabled 'open with paraview' at partvtk finish if it is setup
Now the additional parameters for execution get saved in the batch scripts too.
Implemented details (showing the output) in each post-processing tool.
Started implementing properties. Fixed #5
Fixed a bug where putting an MK value higher than 10 in bounds would set to 10 some fluid ones
Now when changing an object type or creating a new one the lowest MK free is put automatically. Fixes #7
Deleted material related code. Cleaned last commit mess
Updated case summary template to show new executable paths
Added IsoSurface support. Currently working on BoundaryVTK. Fixes #8
Changed the installer to not use threading. Hopefully fixes #9
